      <section eId="sec_4501">
        <num>4501</num>
        <heading>Self-incrimination</heading>
        <content>
          <p>  ยง 4501. Self-incrimination. A competent witness shall not be excused\nfrom answering a relevant question, on the ground only that the answer\nmay tend to establish that he owes a debt or is otherwise subject to a\ncivil suit. This section does not require a witness to give an answer\nwhich will tend to accuse himself of a crime or to expose him to a\npenalty or forfeiture, nor does it vary any other rule respecting the\nexamination of a witness.\n</p>
        </content>
      </section>
